_1.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Vatican_City_dotm_banner_1.jpg/2550px-Vatican_City_dotm_banner_1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/Vatican_City_dotm_banner_1.jpg/3400px-Vatican_City_dotm_banner_1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4436\" data-file-height=\"1479\" width=\"1700\" height=\"567\"></a></span></div>","link":"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Rome/Vatican","retrieved":1670285503014},{"title":"Cooch Behar (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r4523569\">\n<div class=\"banner-image js-proportonal-resize\">\n<p>\t<span class=\"mw-default-size nolink interactiveIcon\" typeof=\"mw:File/Frameless\"><span><img alt=\"Interactive icon.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Interactive_icon.svg/220px-Interactive_icon.svg.png\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Interactive_icon.svg/330px-Interactive_icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Interactive_icon.svg/440px-Interactive_icon.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"133\" data-file-height=\"200\" width=\"220\" height=\"331\"></span></span>\n</p>\n\t<div class=\"mainpage-shadowbox banner-box-2 banner-box-left\">\n\t\t<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cooch_Behar\"><a href=\"/wiki/Cooch_Behar\" title=\"Cooch Behar\">Cooch Behar</a></span></h2>\n\t\t<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Off_the_beaten_path\"><a href=\"/wiki/Previously_Off_the_beaten_path\" title=\"Previously Off the beaten path\">Off the beaten path</a></span></h3>\n\t\t<div class=\"quote\"><a href=\"/wiki/Cooch_Behar\" title=\"Cooch Behar\">Cooch Behar Palace is the main attraction of the city. Every year the Cooch Behar <i>Ras Mela</i> is hosted, which is one of the region's biggest winter carnivals.</a></div>\n\t</div>\n<p>\t<span class=\"nolink\" typeof=\"mw:File/Frameless\"><span title=\"Cooch Behar\"><img alt=\"Cooch Behar\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/Cooch_Behar_Palace_-_Cooch_Behar_-_West_Bengal_-_005_%28cropped2%29.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" data-file-width=\"1700\" data-file-height=\"567\" width=\"1700\" height=\"567\"></span></span>\n</p>\n\t<span typeof=\"mw:File/Frameless\"><a href=\"/wiki/Cooch_Behar\" title=\"Cooch Behar\"><img alt=\"Cooch Behar\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/Cooch_Behar_Palace_-_Cooch_Behar_-_West_Bengal_-_005_%28cropped2%29.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" data-file-width=\"1700\" data-file-height=\"567\" width=\"1700\" height=\"567\"></a></span></div>","link":"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Cooch_Behar","retrieved":1670285503020},{"title":"Georgian cuisine (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r4523569\">\n<div class=\"banner-image js-proportonal-resize\">\n<p>\t<span class=\"mw-default-size nolink interactiveIcon\" typeof=\"mw:File/Frameless\"><span><img alt=\"Interactive icon.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Interactive_icon.svg/220px-Interactive_icon.svg.png\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Interactive_icon.svg/330px-Interactive_icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Interactive_icon.svg/440px-Interactive_icon.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"133\" data-file-height=\"200\" width=\"220\" height=\"331\"></span></span>\n</p>\n\t<div class=\"mainpage-shadowbox banner-box-2 banner-box-left\" style=\"width:50%\">\n\t\t<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Georgian_cuisine\"><a href=\"/wiki/Georgian_cuisine\" title=\"Georgian cuisine\">Georgian cuisine</a></span></h2>\n\t\t<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Featured_travel_topics\"><a href=\"/wiki/Previous_Featured_travel_topics\" title=\"Previous Featured travel topics\">Featured travel topics</a></span></h3>\n\t\t<div class=\"quote\"><a href=\"/wiki/Georgian_cuisine\" title=\"Georgian cuisine\">The cuisine of Georgia has drawn influences from the Silk Road, and is famous abroad for its quality.</a></div>\n\t</div>\n<p>\t<span class=\"nolink\" typeof=\"mw:File/Frameless\"><span title=\"Georgian cuisine\"><img alt=\"Georgian cuisine\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikivoyage/en/thumb/8/87/Georgian_cuisine_banner_1.jpg/1700px-Georgian_cuisine_banner_1.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikivoyage/en/8/87/Georgian_cuisine_banner_1.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"2000\" data-file-height=\"667\" width=\"1700\" height=\"567\"></span></span>\n</p>\n\t<span typeof=\"mw:File/Frameless\"><a href=\"/wiki/Georgian_cuisine\" title=\"Georgian cuisine\"><img alt=\"Georgian cuisine\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikivoyage/en/thumb/8/87/Georgian_cuisine_banner_1.jpg/1700px-Georgian_cuisine_banner_1.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikivoyage/en/8/87/Georgian_cuisine_banner_1.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"2000\" data-file-height=\"667\" width=\"1700\" height=\"567\"></a></span></div>","link":"https://en.wikivoyage.org/wiki/Georgian_cuisine","retrieved":1670285503021}]}